>iterating over the pair of the columns is exactly what the nancorr routines seeks to avoid. can we just directly use that here? this is not scaling very well.

You want to duplicate lines from pd.Series.corr() to pd.DataFrame.corrwith()? What is the reason for that?

This is the `pd.Series.corr()` implementation and it looks just fine to reuse it:
```python
def corr(self, other, method='pearson', min_periods=None):
    this, other = self.align(other, join='inner', copy=False)
    if len(this) == 0:
        return np.nan

    if method in ['pearson', 'spearman', 'kendall']:
        return nanops.nancorr(this.values, other.values, method=method,
                              min_periods=min_periods)
```
